4.00	USCGC_Mellon_(WHEC-717)	USCGC Mellon (WHEC-717)	USCGC Mellon (WHEC-717) is a U. S. Coast Guard high endurance cutter based out of Seattle, Washington. Laid down July 25, 1966 at Avondale Shipyards near New Orleans, Louisiana. Named for Andrew W. Mellon the 49th Secretary of the Treasury from 1921-1932 and launched February 11, 1967 by Mrs. John W. Warner, Jr., sponsor and granddaughter of Andrew Mellon. Mellon was commissioned January 9, 1968. She received her Fleet Rehabilitation and Modernization (FRAM) upgrades from 1985 to 1989.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/USCGC_Mellon_WHEC-717.jpg/300px-USCGC_Mellon_WHEC-717.jpg
